Ukraine’s Mriya Agro Says Its Winter Crops Are in Good Condition

-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 
2011-06-20T15:39:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/ukraine-s-mriya-agro-says-its-winter-crops-are-in-good-condition.html
Mriya Agro Holding Plc, a Ukrainian
agriculture company, said its winter crops are in good condition
and the company expects a “rich” harvest.  Mriya, based in Vasylkivtsi, western Ukraine, increased the
area it has under winter wheat by 82 percent to 120,000 hectares
(296,400 acres), and the area under winter rapeseed by 66
percent to 37,000 hectares, the company said today in an e-
mailed statement.  Mriya raised the total area of land cultivated this year by
10 percent to 240,000 hectares, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
